---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout title="Privacy Policy - Rhymance" pageTitle="Privacy Policy" lastUpdated="December 21, 2030">
	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">1. Introduction</h2>
		<p>
			At Rhymance, we take the privacy of our users very seriously.
			This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, share, and protect your personal
			information when you use our application and services.
		</p>
		<p>
			By using Rhymance, you agree to the practices described in this policy.
			If you do not agree with this policy, please do not use our application.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			2. Information We Collect
		</h2>

		<h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2">
			2.1 Information You Provide
		</h3>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li><strong>Profile information:</strong> Name, age, photos, biography, musical interests, and rhyme preferences.</li>
			<li><strong>Account information:</strong> Email address, phone number (if provided), encrypted password.</li>
			<li><strong>Created content:</strong> Rhymes, lyrics, poems, and other content you create or share on the platform.</li>
			<li><strong>Communications:</strong> Messages you send to other users, as well as communications with our support team.</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">
			2.2 Automatically Collected Information
		</h3>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li><strong>Location data:</strong> With your permission, we collect location information to show you people nearby.</li>
			<li><strong>Device information:</strong> Device type, operating system, unique device identifiers, language settings.</li>
			<li><strong>Usage data:</strong> How you interact with the app, profiles you view, matches made, time spent using the app.</li>
			<li><strong>Cookies and similar technologies:</strong> We use cookies to improve your experience. Check our <a href="/cookies" class="text-passion hover:underline">Cookie Policy</a> for more information.</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">
			2.3 Third-Party Information
		</h3>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li><strong>Social networks:</strong> If you sign up using social media (Facebook, Google, etc.), we will receive basic information from your profile.</li>
			<li><strong>Payment services:</strong> Transaction information (but not credit card data, which is handled by certified payment processors).</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			3. How We Use Your Information
		</h2>
		<p>We use the information collected to:</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li><strong>Provide and improve our services:</strong> Create and manage your account, show compatible profiles, facilitate connections.</li>
			<li><strong>Personalize your experience:</strong> Recommend people based on your preferences and behavior.</li>
			<li><strong>Communicate with you:</strong> Send notifications about matches, messages, app updates, and promotions (you can opt out in settings).</li>
			<li><strong>Security and fraud prevention:</strong> Detect and prevent fraudulent activities, spam, and behaviors that violate our Terms and Conditions.</li>
			<li><strong>Analysis and statistics:</strong> Understand how the application is used to improve functionalities and develop new features.</li>
			<li><strong>Legal compliance:</strong> Comply with legal obligations and respond to legal requests from authorities.</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			4. Sharing Information
		</h2>

		<h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2">
			4.1 With Other Users
		</h3>
		<p>
			Your profile information (photos, name, age, bio, rhymes)
			is visible to other users of the application. Please be careful
			with the personal information you share publicly.
		</p>

		<h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">
			4.2 With Service Providers
		</h3>
		<p>
			We share information with third parties that help us operate our platform, such as:
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li>Hosting and cloud storage services</li>
			<li>Payment processors</li>
			<li>Analytics and marketing services</li>
			<li>Customer support services</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			These providers are contractually obliged to protect your information
			and may only use it to provide services to us.
		</p>

		<h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">
			4.3 For Legal Reasons
		</h3>
		<p>
			We may disclose your information if we believe in good faith that it is necessary to:
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li>Comply with a legal obligation</li>
			<li>Protect the rights, property, or safety of Rhymance, our users, or the public</li>
			<li>Respond to government requests or legal processes</li>
			<li>Prevent fraud or illegal activities</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">
			4.4 Business Transfers
		</h3>
		<p>
			In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your personal information
			may be transferred. We will notify you before your information becomes subject
			to a different privacy policy.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			5. Your Rights and Choices
		</h2>
		<p>
			You have the following rights regarding your personal information:
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li><strong>Access:</strong> You can request a copy of the personal information we hold about you.</li>
			<li><strong>Rectification:</strong> You can update or correct your information at any time from your profile settings.</li>
			<li><strong>Erasure:</strong> You can request the deletion of your account and personal data.</li>
			<li><strong>Objection:</strong> You can object to the processing of your information for certain purposes, such as direct marketing.</li>
			<li><strong>Portability:</strong> You can request to receive your information in a structured, commonly used format.</li>
			<li><strong>Restriction of processing:</strong> You can request that we restrict the processing of your information in certain circumstances.</li>
			<li><strong>Withdraw consent:</strong> Where we have relied on your consent, you can withdraw it at any time.</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			To exercise these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:luismarrer.dev@gmail.com" class="text-passion hover:underline">luismarrer.dev@gmail.com</a>
			or through our <a href="/contact" class="text-passion hover:underline">contact page</a>.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			6. Data Security
		</h2>
		<p>
			We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect
			your personal information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.
			These measures include:
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li>Data encryption in transit and at rest</li>
			<li>Two-factor authentication available</li>
			<li>Strict access controls to personal data</li>
			<li>Regular security audits</li>
			<li>Privacy and security training for our staff</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			However, no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage
			is 100% secure. We do our best to protect your information, but we cannot guarantee
			its absolute security.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			7. Data Retention
		</h2>
		<p>
			We retain your personal information for as long as necessary for the purposes
			described in this policy, unless a longer retention period is required by law.
		</p>
		<p>
			When you delete your account, we will delete or anonymize your personal information
			so that you can no longer be identified, except when we need to retain certain information
			to comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, or enforce our agreements.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			8. Minors
		</h2>
		<p>
			Rhymance is intended for users over 18 years of age. We do not knowingly collect
			personal information from minors. If we discover that we have collected information
			from a minor, we will delete that information immediately.
		</p>
		<p>
			If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal
			information, please contact us immediately.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			9. International Data Transfers
		</h2>
		<p>
			Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your own,
			where data protection laws may differ. When transferring information outside the
			European Economic Area (EEA), we implement appropriate safeguards to ensure your
			information is protected in accordance with GDPR standards.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			10. Links to Third-Party Sites
		</h2>
		<p>
			Our application may contain links to third-party websites or services.
			We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these sites.
			We recommend you read the privacy policies of any third-party sites you visit.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			11. Changes to This Policy
		</h2>
		<p>
			We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices
			or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. We will notify you of
			material changes via an in-app notice or by email.
		</p>
		<p>
			The "Last updated" date at the top of this policy indicates when it was last revised.
			We recommend reviewing this policy periodically.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">12. Contact</h2>
		<p>
			If you have questions, comments, or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data
			practices, you can contact us:
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li><strong>By email:</strong> <a href="mailto:luismarrer.dev@gmail.com" class="text-passion hover:underline">luismarrer.dev@gmail.com</a></li>
			<li><strong>Through our contact form:</strong> <a href="/contact" class="text-passion hover:underline">Contact page</a></li>
			<li><strong>By mail:</strong> Rhymance, Calle Fortaleza 258, Suite 402, San Juan, PR 00901, Puerto Rico</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			If you are not satisfied with our response to your privacy inquiry, you have the right
			to lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			13. Legal Bases for Processing (GDPR)
		</h2>
		<p>
			If you are located in the European Economic Area, we process your personal information
			based on the following legal bases:
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li><strong>Performance of a contract:</strong> To provide our services according to our Terms and Conditions.</li>
			<li><strong>Consent:</strong> When you have given your consent to process your information for specific purposes.</li>
			<li><strong>Legitimate interests:</strong> To improve our services, security, and fraud prevention.</li>
			<li><strong>Legal compliance:</strong> To comply with applicable legal obligations.</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
</LegalLayout>
